data.meta_description:
Curtis Lee Mayfield made his first recordings in 1958 as a member of a Chicago Soul/R & B group, The Impressions. He was 16, from the city’s notorious Cabrini Green Housing Projects. 

Mayfield made his last recording, “New World Order,” in 1995 after four decades of hit-making as a solo artist, producer, composer and as a symbol for Black Pride and Black Capitalism within the music industry. 

Full Bio: https://www.curtismayfield.com/biography.html
